4 Cross-Validation Part II

4.1 Data leak

4.1.1 Sample code

data %>% 
  group_by(worker_id) %>% 
  nest() %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  crossv_mc(100, .2) %>% 
  mutate(train = map(train, ~ as.data.frame(.) %>%
                       unnest(c("data"))),
         test = map(test, ~ as.data.frame(.) %>%
                      unnest(c("data"))))  %>% 
  mutate(model_lin_lin = map(train, ~lm(duration ~ trial, data = .)),
         model_lin_log = map(train, ~lm(duration ~ ltrial, data = .)),
         model_log_lin = map(train, ~lm(lduration ~ trial, data = .)),
         model_log_log = map(train, ~lm(lduration ~ ltrial, data = .))
  ) %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = contains("model"),
               names_to = "model_name",
               values_to = "fit") %>% 
  mutate(tr_r2 = map2_dbl(.x = fit,
                          .y = train,
                          .f = ~ rsquare(.x, .y)),
         tr_rmse = map2_dbl(.x = fit,
                            .y = train,
                            .f = ~ rmse(.x, .y)),
         v_r2 = map2_dbl(.x = fit,
                         .y = test,
                         .f = ~ rsquare(.x, .y)),
         v_rmse = map2_dbl(.x = fit,
                           .y = test,
                           .f = ~ rmse(.x, .y))) %>%
  select(model_name, tr_r2, tr_rmse, v_r2, v_rmse) %>% 
  group_by(model_name) %>% 
  summarize(tr_r2 = mean(tr_r2),
            tr_rmse = mean(tr_rmse),
            v_r2 = mean(v_r2),
            v_rmse = mean(v_rmse)) %>% 
  arrange(v_r2)

#> 2 model_log_lin 0.0865   0.817 0.0904  0.820

4.2 Random effects

4.2.1 Fixed effects only

mixed_effects_loss = function(model, data, loss.f, y_var, fixed_only) {
  target_col <- deparse(substitute(y_var))
  
  if (fixed_only) {
    y_hat = predict(model,
                    newdata = data,
                    allow.new.levels = T,
                    re.form = NA)
  } else {
    y_hat = predict(model, newdata = data)
  }
  
  loss = data %>% 
    mutate(y_hat = y_hat,
           loss = loss.f(.[[target_col]], y_hat)) %>% 
    summarize(loss = mean(loss)) %>% 
    pull(loss)
  return (loss)
}

vector_rmse = function(y, y_hat) {
  mse = mean((y - y_hat)^2)
  return (sqrt(mse))
}

vector_rsquare = function(y, y_hat) {
  rss = sum((y - y_hat)^2)
  tss = sum((y - mean(y))^2)
  return (1 - rss/tss)
}

data %>% 
  filter(correct == T) %>% 
  mutate(trial = trial/64) %>% 
  group_by(worker_id) %>% 
  nest() %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  crossv_kfold(5) %>% 
  mutate(train = map(train, ~ as.data.frame(.) %>%
                       unnest(c("data"))),
         test = map(test, ~ as.data.frame(.) %>%
                      unnest(c("data"))))  %>% 
  mutate(model_log_lin = map(train, ~lmer(lduration ~ trial + (trial | worker_id),
                                          data = .,
                                          control = lmerControl(optimizer ='optimx',
                                                                optCtrl=list(method='nlminb')))),
         model_log_log = map(train, ~lmer(lduration ~ ltrial + (ltrial | worker_id),
                                          data = .,
                                          control = lmerControl(optimizer ='optimx',
                                                                optCtrl=list(method='nlminb'))))
  ) %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = contains("model"),
               names_to = "model_name",
               values_to = "fit") %>% 
  mutate(tr_r2 = map2_dbl(.x = fit,
                          .y = train,
                          .f = ~ mixed_effects_loss(.x, .y, vector_rsquare, lduration, F)),
         tr_rmse = map2_dbl(.x = fit,
                            .y = train,
                            .f = ~ mixed_effects_loss(.x, .y, vector_rmse, lduration, F)),
         v_r2 = map2_dbl(.x = fit,
                         .y = test,
                         .f = ~ mixed_effects_loss(.x, .y, vector_rsquare, lduration, T)),
         v_rmse = map2_dbl(.x = fit,
                           .y = test,
                           .f = ~ mixed_effects_loss(.x, .y, vector_rmse, lduration, T))) %>%
  select(model_name, tr_r2, tr_rmse, v_r2, v_rmse) %>% 
  group_by(model_name) %>% 
  summarize(tr_r2 = mean(tr_r2),
            tr_rmse = mean(tr_rmse),
            v_r2 = mean(v_r2),
            v_rmse = mean(v_rmse))

#> 2 model_log_log 0.573   0.538 0.0432  0.792

4.2.2 First 4 trials

data %>% 
  filter(correct == T) %>% 
  mutate(trial = trial/64) %>% 
  arrange(worker_id, trial) %>% 
  group_by(worker_id) %>% 
  nest() %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  crossv_kfold(5) %>% 
  mutate(test = map(test, ~ as.data.frame(.) %>%
                      unnest(c("data"))),
         heads = map(test, ~ group_by(., worker_id) %>% 
                       top_n(n = 4, wt = -trial) %>% 
                       ungroup()),
         test = map(test, ~ group_by(., worker_id) %>% 
                      top_n(n = nrow(.) - 4, wt = trial) %>% 
                      ungroup()),
         train = map2(.x = train,
                      .y = heads,
                      ~ as.data.frame(.x) %>%
                        unnest(c("data")) %>% 
                        bind_rows(.y)))  %>% 
  mutate(model_log_lin = map(train, ~lmer(lduration ~ trial + (trial | worker_id),
                                          data = .,
                                          control = lmerControl(optimizer ='optimx',
                                                                optCtrl=list(method='nlminb')))),
         model_log_log = map(train, ~lmer(lduration ~ ltrial + (ltrial | worker_id),
                                          data = .,
                                          control = lmerControl(optimizer ='optimx',
                                                                optCtrl=list(method='nlminb'))))
  ) %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = contains("model"),
               names_to = "model_name",
               values_to = "fit") %>% 
  mutate(tr_r2 = map2_dbl(.x = fit,
                          .y = train,
                          .f = ~ mixed_effects_loss(.x, .y, vector_rsquare, lduration, F)),
         tr_rmse = map2_dbl(.x = fit,
                            .y = train,
                            .f = ~ mixed_effects_loss(.x, .y, vector_rmse, lduration, F)),
         v_r2 = map2_dbl(.x = fit,
                         .y = test,
                         .f = ~ mixed_effects_loss(.x, .y, vector_rsquare, lduration, F)),
         v_rmse = map2_dbl(.x = fit,

  select(model_name, tr_r2, tr_rmse, v_r2, v_rmse) %>% 
  group_by(model_name) %>% 
  summarize(tr_r2 = mean(tr_r2),
            tr_rmse = mean(tr_rmse),
            v_r2 = mean(v_r2),

4.3 CV With Logistic Regression

data %>% 
  group_by(worker_id) %>% 
  nest() %>% 
  ungroup() %>%

         model_lin_log = map(train, ~glm(correct ~ ltrial, data = ., family = "binomial")),
         model_log_lin = map(train, ~glm(correct ~ trial, data = ., family = "binomial")),

               names_to = "model_name",

  mutate(tr_r2 = map2_dbl(.x = fit,
                          .y = train,
                          .f = ~ rsquare(.x, .y)),
         tr_rmse = map2_dbl(.x = fit,
                            .y = train,
                            .f = ~ rmse(.x, .y)),
         v_r2 = map2_dbl(.x = fit,
                         .y = test,
                         .f = ~ rsquare(.x, .y)),
         v_rmse = map2_dbl(.x = fit,
                           .y = test,
                           .f = ~ rmse(.x, .y))) %>%
  select(model_name, tr_r2, tr_rmse, v_r2, v_rmse) %>% 
  group_by(model_name) %>% 
  summarize(tr_r2 = mean(tr_r2),

  arrange(v_r2)
#> # A tibble: 4 x 5
#>   model_name    tr_r2 tr_rmse  v_r2 v_rmse
#>   <chr>         <dbl>   <dbl> <dbl>  <dbl>
#> 1 model_lin_log -2.99    1.96 -3.20   1.95
#> 2 model_log_log -2.99    1.96 -3.20   1.95
#> 3 model_lin_lin -2.95    1.94 -3.19   1.94
#> 4 model_log_lin -2.95    1.94 -3.19   1.94
sigmoid = function(x) {
  return (1 / (1 + exp(-x)))
}

cross_entropy = function(y, logit) {
  y_hat = sigmoid(logit)
  ce = -(y * log(y_hat) + (1-y) * log(1 - y_hat))
  return (mean(ce))
}

data %>% 
  group_by(worker_id) %>% 
  nest() %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  crossv_mc(100, .2) %>% 
  mutate(train = map(train, ~ as.data.frame(.) %>%
                       unnest(c("data"))),
         test = map(test, ~ as.data.frame(.) %>%
                      unnest(c("data"))))  %>% 
  mutate(model_lin_lin = map(train, ~glm(correct ~ trial, data = ., family = "binomial")),
         model_lin_log = map(train, ~glm(correct ~ ltrial, data = ., family = "binomial")),
         model_log_lin = map(train, ~glm(correct ~ trial, data = ., family = "binomial")),
         model_log_log = map(train, ~glm(correct ~ ltrial, data = ., family = "binomial"))
  ) %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = contains("model"),
               names_to = "model_name",
               values_to = "fit") %>% 
  mutate(tr_r2 = map2_dbl(.x = fit,
                          .y = train,
                          .f = ~ rsquare(.x, .y)),
         tr_rmse = map2_dbl(.x = fit,
                            .y = train,
                            .f = ~ rmse(.x, .y)),
         v_r2 = map2_dbl(.x = fit,
                         .y = test,
                         .f = ~ rsquare(.x, .y)),
         v_rmse = map2_dbl(.x = fit,
                           .y = test,
                           .f = ~ rmse(.x, .y)),
         tr_ce = map2_dbl(.x = fit,
                          .y = train,
                          .f = ~ cross_entropy(.y$correct,
                                               as.vector(predict(.x, .y)))),
         v_ce = map2_dbl(.x = fit,
                         .y = test,
                         .f = ~ cross_entropy(.y$correct,
                                              as.vector(predict(.x, .y))))) %>%
  select(model_name, tr_r2, tr_rmse, tr_ce, v_r2, v_rmse, v_ce) %>% 
  group_by(model_name) %>% 
  summarize(tr_r2 = mean(tr_r2),
            tr_rmse = mean(tr_rmse),
            tr_ce = mean(tr_ce),
            v_r2 = mean(v_r2),
            v_rmse = mean(v_rmse),
            v_ce = mean(v_ce))

5 Segmented Regression

5.1 Create artificial intervention: one is significant, one is not

set.seed(252)
df.sr.insig = data %>%
  mutate(duration = map2_dbl(.x = duration,
                             .y = correct == T & trial > 16,
                             ~ ifelse(.y,
                                      .x - rnorm(1, 2, 1), .x)),
         lduration = log2(duration),
         post_treat = trial > 16)
df.sr.sig = data %>%
  mutate(duration = map2_dbl(.x = duration,
                             .y = correct == T & trial > 16,
                             ~ ifelse(.y,
                                      .x - rnorm(1, .x/3, 1.2), .x)),
         lduration = log2(duration),
         post_treat = trial > 16)

5.2 Significant results

df.sr.sig %>% 
  filter(correct == T) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = trial, y = lduration)) +
  stat_summary(fun.y = "mean",
               geom = "point",
               alpha = 1,
               size = 1.5) +
